To make it short, one can skip kavacha, argala, keelaka, ratri=
 sooktam and devi sooktam. Just do the 13 chapters and the moola mantra bef=
ore/after a minimal count (say, 28). Still, if one is not comfortable with =
the text, it will take too long. So, before attempting Chandi homam, one ma=
y want to first practice chanting the text. If one can chant the text in 1 =
hour, one can then think of doing homam in 1 hr 15 min or so.
=A0
It is pos=
sible to also split it into multiple days and do 1 or 2 or 3 chapters every=
day and continue next day from there. Still, purnahuti can be given each da=
y.
=A0
It is also possible to do homam with a single verse repeated many ti=
mes or with moola mantra (navarna mantra).
=A0
Instead of rushing and doing=
 all 13 chapters without enjoying them and without any mental focus, it may=
 be better to do just a few chapters, but with mental focus and enjoyment.
=

